CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1956, pg. A1 reads: "Pittsburgh's "Princess Grace" - Pretty Gwendolyn Poinsette represents our own American "princess" in Pittsburgh. She'll attend both the Urban League's "Bal Masque" and the AKA Cotillion. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Gwendolyn Poinsette wearing light colored strapless gown with full tulle skirt, long light colored gloves with wrist corsage, and choker, posed on sofa in interior, possibly Hilton Hotel, with wood paneling and bold floral carpeting
